      "instructions": "Heat the olive oil in deep saute pan. Add the onion, ginger, and garlic; cook 5 minutes, or until soft. Stir in the spices and cook 1 minute. Stir in the tomato paste and flour; cook 1 minute. Add the water, lemon juice, potatoes, and carrots; bring to a simmer. Cook, uncovered, for 20 minutes, or until the vegetables are soft and the liquid thickens (you should have about 4 cups of curry). Season to taste with salt and pepper. Stir in tofu, peas and cilantro.Heat oven to 420F.Roll out the pie crust. Place the bottom crust in a pie pan. Fill with curry and cover with the top crust; crimp the edges. Brush the top pie crust with egg. Cut several slits in the top crust for ventilation.Bake for 30-40 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown.",
