      "instructions": "Preheat the oven to 350.Combine corn, beans, diced onion, diced tomatoes, minced jalapeno, rice, stock, cilantro, salt, chili powder and red pepper flakes in a large bowl. Stir and transfer the mixture into a well seasoned cast iron skillet. Make sure that rice and veggies are evenly distributed throughout the skillet. Place it in the oven for 30-35 minutes, carefully stirring after about 20 minutes. While rice and veggies are cooking, sear chicken tenders with some salt and chili powder on stove top over medium heat. Dice chicken when it cools enough to be handled. To toast tortillas: slice two large tortillas into thin strips, about 2 inches long. Spread them on an ungreased cookie sheet and toast them in the oven until golden, about 2-4 minutes.",
